Package: xEnrich
Title: Multi-Scale Enrichment with Information Theory and Location Context
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Artur", "Shvetcov", , "shvetsov1983@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A unified framework for translating omics results into biological
    context. Provides two complementary analysis tracks: (1) an
    information-theoretic enrichment track that scores gene sets by mutual
    information rather than raw overlap, uses adaptive permutation testing with
    explicit confidence intervals on p-values, and identifies the minimal
    non-redundant set of independent signals via greedy conditional mutual
    information selection; and (2) a location-aware track that maps gene or
    protein lists to enriched organs using Human Protein Atlas data (IHC and
    RNA) and then resolves cell-type origin within those organs using Tabula
    Sapiens single-cell transcriptomes. The two tracks share a common gene-list
    interface and can be combined to answer not only which pathways are altered
    but where in the body and in which cell type the changes are most relevant.
    Reference data (Human Protein Atlas and Tabula Sapiens) is hosted on Zenodo 
    (https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19106109) and cached locally on first use.

